# Cursor Rules for Gradle Modules

These rules must always be applied when working with modules.

## Module Creation
When creating a new module, always use the script:
./modules.sh createModule <MODULE-NAME>

This ensures:
- Proper module directory structure creation
- Correct version property addition to gradle.properties
- Module list updates

## Module Removal
When removing a module, always use the script:
./modules.sh removeModule <MODULE-NAME>

This ensures:
- Complete module directory removal
- Proper version property removal from gradle.properties
- Module list updates
